messages.text: He said he'd hack SafeHaven and delete my records.

In our first session, you said it was him or you.
Jack, you need to call the police.

Remember how we talked about boundaries?
But I still feel connected to you somehow.
I killed that lady, Dr. Took.
I let my brother get behind the wheel three months ago.
But I knew I had to save you.
I shot him in the mouth.

I feel very firm about this.

Dr. Took. I'm Dr. Took to you.

I don't know what's wrong with me, Hortence.

I'm afraid at this point I could be a danger to myself.

And then six years in forced military service while in exile.

To you, to that poor lady.

But you need to get more help.
Be honest with the prison doctors and psychologists.

Epilogueâ€”The Elk County police arrested Jack Dwyer without incident on February 16. He is currently incarcerated in the Stoker State Penitentiary.
Dr. Hortence Took soon resigned as a SafeHaven therapist and opened a private practice at an office in her hometown, where she continues to treat her clients with professionalism and great empathy.
Edwin Dwyer is buried in the Elk County Cemetery.
On March 15, Jack Dwyer began his job as a clerk in the Stoker State Penitentiary Library.
He is currently writing his own novel, "Redemption."
